#~ msgid ""
#~ "Welcome to &kate;, a programmer's text editor for &kde; version 2.2 and "
#~ "above. Some of &kate;'s many features include configurable syntax "
#~ "highlighting for languages ranging from C and C++ to <acronym>HTML</"
#~ "acronym> to bash scripts, the ability to create and maintain projects, a "
#~ "multiple document interface (<acronym>MDI</acronym>), and a self-"
#~ "contained terminal emulator."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Wamkelekile ku &kate;, umhleli wokubhaliweyo wabadwelisi we &kde; "
#~ "uguqulelo 2.2 na ngaphezulu. Eminye ye &kate;imisebenzi emininzi iquka "
#~ "isivakalisi esiqwalaselweyo uphawulo lwelwimi ukusuka ku C no C++ ukuya "
#~ "<acronym>HTML</acronym> ukunqgubanisa izishicilelo, indlela yokwenza "
#~ "nokulondoloza iiprojekti, oluninzi ujongano loxwebhu (<acronym>MDI</"
#~ "acronym>), noziqulathe-ngokwakhe umlinganisi wendlela yesiphelo."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "But &kate; is more than a programmer's editor. Its ability to open "
#~ "several files at once makes it ideal for editing &UNIX;'s many "
#~ "configuration files. This document was written in &kate;."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Kodwa &kate; ingaphezu komhleli wabadwelisi. Yindlela yokuvula ezininzi "
#~ "iifayile kubekanye kuyenza ilungele ukuhlela &UNIX; ezininzi iifayile "
#~ "zoqwalaselo. Olu xwebhu labhalwa kwi &kate;."

